{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17655548","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17655548"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:03:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:03:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18666"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18666","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18666"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11398"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77414"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11398"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18666"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62921"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7270"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26411"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26613"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77414"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe muscles of facial expression around the eyes and forehead are important for conveying emotions and protecting the eyes. These muscles are innervated by the facial nerve.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the action of the corrugator supercilii muscle?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Draws eyebrows medially and downward","Compresses the lacrimal sac","Elevates the eyebrows","Closes the eyelids","Creates horizontal forehead wrinkles"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edraws eyebrows medially and downward\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary action of the corrugator supercilii muscle (image). This creates vertical furrows between the eyebrows and is associated with frowning or expressing concern.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECompresses the lacrimal sac\u003C/strong\u003E - This is performed by the lacrimal part of the orbicularis oculi muscle\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElevates the eyebrows\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the action of the frontalis muscle\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECloses the eyelids\u003C/strong\u003E - This is performed by the palpebral part of the orbicularis oculi muscle\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreates horizontal forehead wrinkles\u003C/strong\u003E - This is another action of the frontalis muscle when it contracts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAll these muscles are innervated by branches of the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII) and work together to create facial expressions and protect the eyes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The corrugator supercilii muscle draws the eyebrows medially and downward to create a furrowed expression.","The frontalis muscle elevates the eyebrows and creates horizontal forehead wrinkles.","The orbicularis oculi has orbital and palpebral parts that close the eyelids and compress the lacrimal sac."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cCorrugator supercilii muscle frontal\u201d by Anatomography\u00a0is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 2.1 jp Unported license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.1/jp/deed.en). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Corrugator_supercilii_muscle_frontal.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62921"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18666"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21424"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21424"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/RAJFcMjByxOATPl39pgRTehurMUklQ.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/RAJFcMjByxOATPl39pgRTehurMUklQ.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":640}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62921","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62921"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-06T22:22:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-06T22:22:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11398"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77414"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt